WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:04.754
NARRATOR: Previously on
Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles:

00:04.922 --> 00:09.759
SARAH: There's a warehouse in the desert.
They're building something there. Metal.

00:09.927 --> 00:11.511
-Who are you?
-My name's Winston.

00:11.679 --> 00:12.762
Where's the metal?

00:17.643 --> 00:20.061
DEREK: I talked to your mom.
She found something.

00:20.229 --> 00:23.356
-Is it real this time?
-I detected this audio transmission...

00:23.524 --> 00:26.651
-...on an unsecured line.
MAN: Breach. Man shot at Heat and Air.

00:26.819 --> 00:28.778
Shut the place down.

00:30.447 --> 00:34.117
You mind telling me
where you keep your demolition materials?

00:36.745 --> 00:40.748
I hate funerals. Mom, everybody who
knew anything about the factory is dead.

00:40.916 --> 00:42.750
-Well, I'm not.
DIANA: Winston.

00:42.918 --> 00:44.711
Did you know my husband, Sarah?

00:44.878 --> 00:47.296
The whole place was wired. Every house.

00:47.464 --> 00:50.049
Every move anyone ever made
was being watched.

00:50.259 --> 00:53.553
You're tired. You've been sick.
Chasing killer robots will do that.

00:56.432 --> 00:58.933
SARAH:
Midnight is the witching hour.

01:00.269 --> 01:04.814
If you believe that kind of thing,
and most people won't admit it if they do...

01:07.151 --> 01:10.528
...midnight is the time when a door
opens from our world into the next...

01:10.696 --> 01:14.365
...and we are visited by dark spirits
of the shadow lands.

01:15.325 --> 01:21.122
The incubus, the succubus, the old hag.
Visitors are known by many names...

01:21.290 --> 01:23.499
...but each story bears the same marks.

01:25.961 --> 01:29.338
The demons come after midnight
in the first three hours of the new day...

01:29.506 --> 01:33.468
...when we are alone and vulnerable,
deep asleep and helpless.

01:33.635 --> 01:34.677
When we cannot move.

01:35.846 --> 01:40.975
They lay on us, press on us, suffocate us,
take from us what is most precious.

01:42.436 --> 01:47.023
Our lives, our love, our sanity.

01:47.566 --> 01:49.484
Our sleep.

01:52.654 --> 01:55.323
If you believe in that kind of thing.

02:03.499 --> 02:04.540
John.

02:04.708 --> 02:06.000
[PHONE BEEPS]

02:06.418 --> 02:07.877
Where are you?

02:08.045 --> 02:10.880
SARAH:
In an industrial park near downtown.

02:11.048 --> 02:13.549
Mom, it's almost 12.
I was hoping you were asleep.

02:14.009 --> 02:16.052
Well, it didn't take.

02:16.595 --> 02:18.596
JOHN:
What are you doing?

02:19.097 --> 02:22.016
I got a lead off the surveillance tapes
of Charm Acres.

02:22.184 --> 02:24.769
Yeah, how many hours of people
sleeping did you watch?

02:24.978 --> 02:26.062
All of them.

02:26.772 --> 02:28.397
JOHN:
So who are you?

02:28.565 --> 02:29.982
SARAH:
Western Iron and Metal.

02:30.192 --> 02:33.444
They supplied metal tooling equipment
to Desert Heat and Air.

02:34.196 --> 02:36.030
You think they're connected to Skynet.

02:36.198 --> 02:38.699
Get on the computer,
find out who owns the place.

02:38.867 --> 02:39.909
I'm on it.

02:53.924 --> 02:55.925
[CLATTERING]

03:19.950 --> 03:21.951
[ELECTRICAL BUZZING]

03:32.629 --> 03:34.630
[GASPING]

03:37.968 --> 03:39.260
HOBSON:
Sarah.

03:39.428 --> 03:41.053
Sarah.

03:41.221 --> 03:43.556
Sarah. You had another nightmare.

03:43.765 --> 03:46.100
I can't stay here anymore.

03:47.102 --> 03:50.229
-You've only been here one night.
-Feels a lot longer.

03:50.397 --> 03:53.065
We don't have enough data
to prescribe a treatment.

03:53.233 --> 03:56.152
-The first night establishes a baseline.
-I'll be fine.

03:56.361 --> 03:59.113
You go home now,
things will only get worse.

03:59.740 --> 04:03.200
You think two weeks without sleep
is bad? Try two or three years.

04:03.368 --> 04:04.410
It happens.

04:05.913 --> 04:07.872
Everyone needs their sleep.

04:08.081 --> 04:09.248
Not everyone.

04:09.416 --> 04:11.626
You do.

04:11.835 --> 04:14.253
I'm going to get you coffee.
But I have to warn you.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.714
This is a decaf only facility, all right?

04:17.674 --> 04:19.091
Hmm.

04:20.302 --> 04:22.303
[LIGHTER CLICKING]

04:29.061 --> 04:30.561
[IN BRITISH ACCENT]
Can I help you?

04:30.729 --> 04:31.771
Who are you?

04:31.980 --> 04:34.815
I'm your roommate. Dana.

04:35.817 --> 04:36.859
When did you get here?

04:37.027 --> 04:39.695
I checked in last night
while you were asleep.

04:39.863 --> 04:43.324
Well, not really asleep. More like
thrashing and screaming in your bed.

04:44.952 --> 04:46.118
What's with the lighter?

04:47.204 --> 04:49.747
-What lighter?
-The one in your bra.

04:51.416 --> 04:53.834
I'm trying to give up smoking.

04:54.044 --> 04:57.213
-In a sleep clinic.
-Yeah, I've got sleep problems too.

04:57.422 --> 04:59.966
The doctors think it's related
to my chronic fatigue.

05:00.133 --> 05:02.259
Which was caused by my eating disorder.

05:02.427 --> 05:06.430
Which is why I had the lap band surgery.
You know, the staple in your stomach.

05:07.224 --> 05:11.727
But are the doctors satisfied
with that? No.

05:12.145 --> 05:15.022
They want to take away all my vices.

05:15.440 --> 05:17.525
Well, that's not gonna happen.

05:17.693 --> 05:21.404
-A girl's gotta sin sometime.
-Hence the smoking.

05:21.947 --> 05:23.990
Yeah, that and the younger men.

05:24.199 --> 05:26.200
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

05:26.702 --> 05:29.161
-Mom.
-Hey, Tiger.

05:30.122 --> 05:32.873
Hello. Uh.... Ahem.

05:33.041 --> 05:35.292
It's visiting time.
Cameron's in the cafeteria.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.211
DANA [WHISPERING]:
Hey. Do me a favor.

05:37.838 --> 05:39.672
Let's keep this our little secret.

05:48.223 --> 05:50.641
Scrambled or hard boiled?

05:50.809 --> 05:51.851
Scrambled.

05:52.060 --> 05:56.188
You need a carbohydrate that makes
up 15 percent of your daily allowance.

05:57.315 --> 05:59.233
Those won't be as good as yours.

06:02.738 --> 06:04.071
You made pancakes?

06:04.656 --> 06:07.033
I added a teaspoon of vanilla
to your recipe.

06:07.200 --> 06:10.786
-I don't have a recipe.
-The recipe on the box.

06:20.756 --> 06:22.506
Not as good as hers?

06:22.716 --> 06:24.300
Not as good as food.

06:24.468 --> 06:27.178
Tomorrow, I'll bring you
something real to eat.

06:27.804 --> 06:30.139
-They have anything to say?
-About what?

06:30.307 --> 06:32.933
About what?
About why you're not sleeping.

06:33.101 --> 06:34.518
They figured out why?

06:34.728 --> 06:37.229
Besides the fact
the world's about to end?

06:38.523 --> 06:39.940
You used to sleep well.

06:40.525 --> 06:43.152
I shouldn't be here. I should be at home.

06:43.779 --> 06:46.113
We're fine at home. Everything's fine.

06:46.323 --> 06:47.323
[SCOFFS]

06:47.491 --> 06:49.408
This was a mistake.

06:50.243 --> 06:53.496
No, this-- This is necessary.

06:55.082 --> 06:56.707
Mom...

06:57.542 --> 06:59.168
...you're useless like this.

06:59.377 --> 07:01.712
Look at yourself.
You haven't slept in two weeks.

07:01.880 --> 07:03.255
You fell down the stairs.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.842
If you don't take care of yourself,
something worse might happen.

07:07.010 --> 07:09.220
You need to get better.

07:10.305 --> 07:11.806
I need you to get better.

07:15.852 --> 07:17.478
Don't forget.

07:20.482 --> 07:21.607
You're not her.

07:24.402 --> 07:26.779
Please, get some sleep.

07:58.854 --> 08:00.479
[GASPS]

08:03.859 --> 08:05.860
[ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING OVER STEREO]

08:24.963 --> 08:26.255
[ENGINE AND MUSIC STOP]

08:29.009 --> 08:30.426
[DOOR SLAMS]

08:33.805 --> 08:34.847
[DOOR OPENS]

08:41.938 --> 08:42.980
You're dead.

08:44.524 --> 08:47.651
-I killed you.
-And I killed you.

08:50.739 --> 08:53.407
One of us is gonna have to step it up.

08:56.244 --> 08:57.578
[GRUNTS]

09:14.179 --> 09:16.180
So.

09:17.057 --> 09:19.308
You want to know who I am?

09:22.562 --> 09:24.355
It's the first thing most people ask.

09:24.522 --> 09:27.858
First thing out of their mouths when
the gag comes off. "Who are you?"

09:28.026 --> 09:31.111
And they keep asking it
over and over again.

09:33.406 --> 09:38.744
Psychiatrists say naming things
gives people power over them.

09:38.912 --> 09:40.454
They're dead wrong on that.

09:41.623 --> 09:43.624
I already know who you are.

09:43.833 --> 09:46.126
Oh, yeah. Right. I forgot.

09:46.294 --> 09:52.007
And you found Western Iron and Metal.

09:56.263 --> 09:57.304
[WHIMPERS]

09:57.472 --> 10:02.768
Course, I wouldn't expect anything less
from the girl that used a cross-dresser...

10:02.936 --> 10:05.854
...and a hypno-therapist to find us.

10:06.022 --> 10:08.941
You know, I gotta admit,
I didn't see that one coming.

10:10.318 --> 10:12.319
You won't see
the next one coming, either.

10:12.529 --> 10:14.863
No, no. I beg to differ, ma'am.
I beg to differ.

10:15.073 --> 10:17.366
So who do you work for?

10:17.534 --> 10:18.784
I work alone.

10:19.369 --> 10:23.247
Somebody blew up our factory
while you were getting patched up.

10:24.374 --> 10:26.292
Was that your boyfriend on the phone?

10:26.501 --> 10:31.297
What are you guys, some kind of
a Bonnie-and-Clyde-type operation?

10:35.302 --> 10:38.304
I said, was that your Clyde on the phone?

10:41.891 --> 10:43.976
Why don't you come closer
and l'll tell you?

10:44.477 --> 10:48.647
So you can bite my face off?
No. I don't think so.

10:51.818 --> 10:53.777
See those seeds?

10:56.448 --> 10:59.408
I go through about a bag in three hours.

10:59.909 --> 11:02.328
Little habit I picked up
when I quit smoking.

11:03.580 --> 11:07.833
Before I finish that bag,
you're gonna talk.

11:08.001 --> 11:09.043
Special recipe.

11:09.627 --> 11:11.003
Uhn.

11:11.880 --> 11:14.673
It'll have you singing like Sunday choir.

11:21.723 --> 11:23.265
What's wrong? Gel too cold?

11:24.559 --> 11:26.894
Most people don't like
the electrodes first time.

11:27.062 --> 11:30.731
Makes them feel like Frankenstein.
You'll get used to it.

11:30.899 --> 11:34.526
-I'm willing to bet you sleep better tonight.
-What's happening to me?

11:35.862 --> 11:37.780
Let me show you something.

11:40.492 --> 11:43.827
These are our observation machines.

11:45.705 --> 11:47.206
And this is your chart.

11:48.083 --> 11:50.084
There are five stages to the sleep cycle.

11:50.251 --> 11:53.379
The fifth stage is the most active.
Increased respiration rate...

11:53.546 --> 11:55.839
-...blood pressure, brain activity.
-REM sleep.

11:56.007 --> 11:57.508
When most dreaming occurs.

11:58.259 --> 12:02.513
It's rare, but sometimes night terrors
like the ones you're experiencing can--

12:02.680 --> 12:04.848
I never said I was experiencing
night terrors.

12:05.058 --> 12:08.852
You didn't have to. Your chart tells us
everything we need to know.

12:09.020 --> 12:11.188
Night terrors can be caused
by a brain tumor.

12:12.565 --> 12:13.607
Cancer.

12:13.817 --> 12:18.112
Which, far as we can tell, you don't have.
MRI showed your brain was clear.

12:18.279 --> 12:22.116
No heart disease, nocturnal asthma,
or sleep apnea.

12:22.659 --> 12:24.993
What's wrong with you is in your head.

12:25.203 --> 12:28.080
And by your head, I mean your mind.

12:28.248 --> 12:30.958
Therapy to reduce anxiety
is part of the usual treatment.

12:31.126 --> 12:33.168
Have you ever seen a therapist?

12:33.336 --> 12:36.004
A lot of people find talking one on one
to be helpful...

12:36.172 --> 12:39.216
-...in breaking down what's going on.
-I tried it. Didn't take.

12:39.426 --> 12:42.302
How about a prescription?
Diazepam usually helps.

12:42.512 --> 12:43.595
Don't like drugs.

12:44.806 --> 12:49.268
Speaking of drugs, has your roommate
been smoking again?

12:53.648 --> 12:55.816
I'm not interested in being
anybody's mother.

12:55.984 --> 12:58.694
I've got two kids of my own
and that's enough.

13:05.034 --> 13:06.201
Did you know about this?

13:08.204 --> 13:11.415
Besides all the other obvious hazards,
nicotine is a stimulant.

13:11.624 --> 13:14.251
Hits the brain in seconds,
adds 20 heartbeats per minute.

13:14.419 --> 13:18.130
I quit smoking years ago.
I've got too much excitement in my life.

13:18.298 --> 13:19.339
[CHUCKLES]

13:19.507 --> 13:21.049
Yeah, don't we all?

13:21.926 --> 13:24.887
Well, I have to file a report on this.

13:26.764 --> 13:28.932
I'll be back later
to attach your electrodes.

13:46.409 --> 13:50.370
It's a dreamcatcher.
It's supposed to catch nightmares.

13:50.538 --> 13:51.997
Hector made me one too.

13:52.207 --> 13:54.583
-Hector?
-The cleaning guy.

13:54.751 --> 13:58.128
You know, papi chulo
with the neck tattoo.

13:59.964 --> 14:01.089
You look tired.

14:02.217 --> 14:04.051
You should take that as a compliment.

14:06.596 --> 14:08.805
I ran into Nurse Ratched in the hallway.

14:09.015 --> 14:13.977
She smacked my bum for the cigarette
and gave me some sleeping pills.

14:15.396 --> 14:16.605
The good stuff.

14:17.899 --> 14:20.108
So, what about you?

14:20.276 --> 14:22.694
Drowning? Being chased?
Teeth falling out?

14:22.904 --> 14:24.905
Being chased should probably cover it.

14:25.114 --> 14:28.575
You're running away from something
you don't want to deal with.

14:28.743 --> 14:30.410
Least that's what they say, anyway.

14:31.913 --> 14:33.288
And you?

14:33.456 --> 14:37.543
Oh, I burn alive. Yeah, my whole body
just catches on fire.

14:37.710 --> 14:40.087
I try and I try
and I can't put myself out.

14:40.296 --> 14:45.509
-Anxiety about quitting smoking.
-That, or I was a witch in another life.

14:46.344 --> 14:50.138
They say if you die in your dreams,
you die in real life.

14:51.724 --> 14:54.601
Oh, I've died a thousand times.

14:55.061 --> 14:56.937
Never gets any easier.

14:58.648 --> 15:00.274
For all nightmares it's caught...

15:00.441 --> 15:03.360
...I'm surprised it hasn't spilled them
out all over the bed.

15:05.613 --> 15:07.614
Do the bad guys ever catch you?

15:11.452 --> 15:12.494
[ELECTRICAL BUZZING]

15:23.089 --> 15:25.007
[INHALES DEEPLY]

15:31.431 --> 15:34.600
That's quite a collection.

15:35.560 --> 15:38.228
Bullet wounds. Stabbings.

15:41.608 --> 15:43.150
Emergency C-section.

15:50.283 --> 15:53.076
But that's plenty old, that last one.

15:53.953 --> 15:57.623
Your child must be 15,
maybe 20 by now.

16:01.294 --> 16:03.503
They'll kill you.

16:03.671 --> 16:05.547
Just like they killed everyone else.

16:06.174 --> 16:08.800
-They?
-Your bosses. Kaliba.

16:10.970 --> 16:14.848
They blew up your factory.
Killed 30 of their own people.

16:15.058 --> 16:16.767
Lady, you're insane.

16:16.976 --> 16:20.312
Why would anyone blow up
their own factory?

16:20.855 --> 16:22.356
To hide what you were building.

16:22.565 --> 16:23.899
And what was that?

16:24.734 --> 16:26.526
The End.

16:27.236 --> 16:30.030
You're very dramatic.

16:34.702 --> 16:35.744
Diana...

16:39.040 --> 16:40.582
...thought you were a good man.

16:44.545 --> 16:46.880
What do you think she'd say
if she saw you now?

16:49.801 --> 16:51.551
You--

16:53.012 --> 16:55.555
You leave my wife out of this...

16:55.723 --> 16:58.642
...you crazy bitch.

17:00.269 --> 17:01.728
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

17:54.115 --> 17:55.824
Dana.

17:57.285 --> 18:03.165
Dana, wake up.

18:34.739 --> 18:53.882
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

19:01.015 --> 19:02.974
[KEYPAD CHIRPING]

19:51.023 --> 19:52.649
[CURTAIN OPENING]

19:55.111 --> 19:58.905
Your electrodes came off last night.
Did you take them off?

19:59.949 --> 20:01.199
I don't remember.

20:02.451 --> 20:03.618
Are you a sleepwalker?

20:04.453 --> 20:05.829
It's happened once or twice.

20:07.206 --> 20:09.332
You didn't mention that in your intake.

20:09.500 --> 20:11.418
It must have slipped my mind. I'm sorry.

20:11.627 --> 20:14.254
So you don't remember
getting out of bed last night?

20:17.466 --> 20:19.968
I don't remember anything.

20:30.021 --> 20:32.314
Salvador Dali often explored the
subconscious...

20:32.481 --> 20:35.108
...and the dream world in his work.

20:35.943 --> 20:37.986
Are your dreams like this painting?

20:41.240 --> 20:43.366
Everyone's dreams are different.

20:43.534 --> 20:45.744
Guess it depends on
what's stuck in your head.

20:53.252 --> 20:55.170
Gaah-- Come on.

20:55.338 --> 20:56.671
What's it like to dream?

20:58.007 --> 20:59.257
Oh....

20:59.425 --> 21:01.092
Um....

21:02.553 --> 21:06.014
It's sort of like you're in a play
or a movie...

21:06.182 --> 21:09.392
...and it looks real and it feels real.

21:10.519 --> 21:11.978
How do you know it's not real?

21:13.022 --> 21:14.189
Sometimes you don't.

21:17.526 --> 21:18.526
[POUNDING ON GLASS]

21:18.694 --> 21:20.445
[JOHN GRUNTS]

21:20.738 --> 21:22.614
[SIGHS]

21:25.326 --> 21:27.494
Hey. Hey. Be careful.

21:29.205 --> 21:31.539
[COINS CLINKING]

21:32.500 --> 21:34.209
Yes, thank you.

21:36.379 --> 21:37.796
John.

21:39.006 --> 21:40.048
What's wrong?

21:49.558 --> 21:51.226
Something strange is going on here.

21:52.186 --> 21:53.228
Like what?

21:53.396 --> 21:58.733
I woke up last night and saw the nurse
giving my roommate a shot.

22:00.820 --> 22:05.407
Okay, well, it's a medical clinic.
So, what's strange about that?

22:05.616 --> 22:09.077
She was passed out.
She'd already taken sleeping pills.

22:10.955 --> 22:16.418
So you think the nurse is, what,
like the angel of death?

22:16.627 --> 22:20.046
After she gave her the shot,
she went to a room in the basement.

22:27.763 --> 22:29.764
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

22:32.268 --> 22:33.768
Well, she looks all right.

22:33.936 --> 22:36.271
No, she's not.

22:37.481 --> 22:39.482
No one is.

22:42.153 --> 22:43.945
Mom.

22:44.572 --> 22:45.780
Did you sleep last night?

22:45.948 --> 22:47.741
You think I'm making this up?

22:47.908 --> 22:52.287
No. I don't think you're making this up.
It's just--

22:53.289 --> 22:54.372
You're a mess.

22:54.582 --> 22:57.000
Don't be fooled, John.

22:57.251 --> 23:00.128
Don't be fooled by anyone's face.

23:01.130 --> 23:03.465
You don't know
what's behind anyone's face.

23:04.800 --> 23:06.885
You're talking about
the guy at the factory.

23:10.973 --> 23:12.807
The one who shot you.

23:12.975 --> 23:14.601
The one you shot.

23:14.810 --> 23:16.644
We don't talk about that.

23:16.812 --> 23:20.148
-We can talk about anything.
-No, we can't.

23:21.984 --> 23:23.610
Is he the one in your nightmares?

23:27.531 --> 23:31.326
It's always the same.
He comes out of nowhere. He grabs me.

23:33.996 --> 23:35.538
Takes me hostage in a van.

23:40.669 --> 23:42.670
What does he want?

23:44.131 --> 23:48.009
To know who I am. Who I'm
working with. He has me tied up.

23:48.177 --> 23:49.719
Drugged.

23:50.304 --> 23:51.471
He isn't real.

23:52.348 --> 23:54.349
He can't hurt you anymore.

23:54.517 --> 23:58.686
He's in my head, and I can't get him out.

23:59.855 --> 24:01.314
Look at me.

24:03.818 --> 24:08.363
You did what you had to do.
You defended yourself.

24:11.200 --> 24:14.702
I'm not supposed to defend myself.

24:15.037 --> 24:17.705
I'm supposed to defend you.

24:17.957 --> 24:19.582
HOBSON:
Nap time.

24:21.335 --> 24:24.045
Don't worry. We'll get her
to close her eyes. Come on.

24:44.066 --> 24:45.150
[GASPS, GROANS]

24:47.403 --> 24:49.112
My wife.

24:50.239 --> 24:53.074
What was she wearing? At my funeral.

24:53.242 --> 24:55.285
Black.

24:55.536 --> 24:59.581
Hair down or back?

24:59.748 --> 25:01.624
Down. And earrings. Pearls.

25:02.877 --> 25:04.878
I bought those for her birthday.

25:05.087 --> 25:06.546
Salary must be good.

25:08.424 --> 25:09.883
It's the best part of the job.

25:10.593 --> 25:11.634
And the worst?

25:14.054 --> 25:15.597
You saw the tapes.

25:15.806 --> 25:16.931
-Yeah.
-So you know.

25:17.099 --> 25:18.766
Yes.

25:22.897 --> 25:24.606
The first one was the hardest.

25:25.274 --> 25:27.025
Frank?

25:27.902 --> 25:30.236
Your neighbor. His son played lacrosse.

25:30.905 --> 25:35.950
He borrowed my lawn mower
every Friday.

25:36.785 --> 25:37.869
[SIGHS]

25:38.037 --> 25:40.121
He never cleaned the bag.

25:40.331 --> 25:42.624
Why would they want him dead?

25:43.125 --> 25:48.630
He kept the books.
Handled the overseas business.

25:49.006 --> 25:50.173
He was a drunk.

25:50.341 --> 25:52.550
Overseas? So your bosses are foreign.

25:53.802 --> 25:56.846
They fixed me up after you shot me.

25:57.473 --> 25:59.766
Put me in a private clinic.

26:00.142 --> 26:04.145
And I thought it was
because they were being kind.

26:04.313 --> 26:06.481
Then I realized.

26:06.649 --> 26:09.150
They're just patching me up
so I can do my job.

26:09.360 --> 26:10.944
What's your job?

26:12.363 --> 26:14.364
Like I said...

26:14.990 --> 26:16.658
...the first one was the hardest.

26:18.702 --> 26:20.119
You were my first.

26:22.790 --> 26:24.624
Seem surprised.

26:24.833 --> 26:29.295
Well, I just figured,
a bad-ass gal like yourself--

26:29.463 --> 26:31.130
Never.

26:32.675 --> 26:36.511
Well, I'm glad I didn't break your streak.

26:41.600 --> 26:43.851
I can help you disappear.
You and your wife.

26:45.437 --> 26:49.190
Hmm. They'll hunt us down.
They'll slaughter us.

26:49.400 --> 26:52.819
There are ways to keep them off
your trail. Things I've learned.

26:54.363 --> 26:56.197
-Like what?
-You ditch the van.

26:56.365 --> 26:59.534
Get a new car.
Check into an expensive hotel.

26:59.702 --> 27:03.371
The most expensive you can find.
They'll always expect the opposite.

27:03.539 --> 27:05.248
You have my phone.

27:05.749 --> 27:08.251
When I get back to my people,
I'll call you.

27:09.044 --> 27:12.005
But we have to move fast
so they don't know what's happening.

27:18.429 --> 27:20.346
Her smell.

27:22.558 --> 27:26.561
It's what I miss the most.
Like clean laundry.

28:01.597 --> 28:03.014
Aah!

28:04.058 --> 28:06.684
Oh! You didn't see that one coming? Hmm?

28:06.852 --> 28:08.853
[ALARM BLARING]

28:09.772 --> 28:11.773
[ALARM BLARING, FIRE CRACKLING]

28:14.777 --> 28:16.110
Dana.

28:17.780 --> 28:19.280
HOBSON: Get out of the room.
-Dana.

28:19.448 --> 28:20.948
Get out of the room.

28:21.116 --> 28:23.826
-She's in there. She's in there.
-Get her out of the way.

28:23.994 --> 28:27.830
-Is she in there? She's in there.
MAN: Come on.

28:33.337 --> 28:34.962
Hello?

28:35.130 --> 28:38.091
Remember I told you something strange
was going on?

28:43.972 --> 28:45.640
Uh, the-- The nurse.

28:45.891 --> 28:46.974
My roommate's dead.

28:47.142 --> 28:49.477
She died last night in a fire.

28:49.645 --> 28:52.063
They're trying to claim
it's some accident.

28:52.231 --> 28:53.898
Maybe you should come home.

28:54.108 --> 28:56.109
No. Not now.

28:59.488 --> 29:01.572
[WOMAN COUGHS, CLEARS THROAT]

29:01.740 --> 29:04.951
First of all, I'd like to give you an update
on Dana's condition.

29:05.119 --> 29:08.079
There's a rumor going around
that she didn't pull through.

29:08.831 --> 29:14.001
That's not the case. Dana is in extremely
critical condition, but she is still alive.

29:14.253 --> 29:17.755
This has been a traumatic experience
for all of us.

29:18.424 --> 29:21.843
Patients, if you choose to leave the clinic,
you may return any time...

29:22.010 --> 29:25.763
...to complete your treatment.
However, it would be of great value to us...

29:25.931 --> 29:30.685
...and to you, if we were to evaluate
your sleep patterns during this duress.

29:30.936 --> 29:34.772
Whatever you choose,
we fully support your decision.

29:35.357 --> 29:37.358
[CROWD MURMURING]

29:40.028 --> 29:41.696
HOBSON:
Ms. Baum.

29:42.448 --> 29:44.532
I hear you've decided to stay.

29:45.284 --> 29:46.367
I have.

29:46.535 --> 29:50.955
An incident like this increases cortisol.
You may find it more difficult to sleep.

29:51.165 --> 29:52.206
Here.

29:53.709 --> 29:55.042
These should help.

29:56.462 --> 29:57.628
Diazepam.

29:57.838 --> 30:00.715
Like I said,
standard treatment for insomnia.

30:01.842 --> 30:03.509
You should take them now.

30:14.938 --> 30:16.314
Good.

30:36.460 --> 30:38.085
I've been meaning to say thank you.

30:40.005 --> 30:42.006
For the dreamcatcher.

30:42.758 --> 30:44.425
You make them for all the patients?

30:44.968 --> 30:46.385
Just the ones who need them.

30:46.887 --> 30:49.222
The ones who have nightmares.

30:51.475 --> 30:53.059
Did you know her well?

30:53.769 --> 30:55.102
She ain't dead.

30:55.354 --> 30:57.730
Right. Sorry.

30:59.691 --> 31:02.276
She kept saying she dreamt
she died in a fire.

31:04.613 --> 31:06.739
Maybe I should have made
her a bigger one.

31:06.949 --> 31:09.075
Nightmare didn't burn her.
A cigarette did.

31:11.245 --> 31:13.621
She should've taken charge.

31:14.039 --> 31:15.122
Taken charge?

31:15.290 --> 31:19.126
Of what was going on inside her head.
Controlled it.

31:19.294 --> 31:21.462
-You believe it, then?
-Of course I do.

31:30.264 --> 31:33.307
Coyote.
Does it have mystical significance?

31:33.809 --> 31:36.060
Does it protect you? Guide you?

31:36.270 --> 31:38.896
This? No.

31:39.106 --> 31:42.400
This was for my girl. She thinks it's sexy.

31:53.662 --> 31:55.997
-Tell me a story.
-Go to hell.

31:56.331 --> 31:57.748
Ha.

31:58.792 --> 32:01.669
What most people know
about torture is bullcrap.

32:01.837 --> 32:06.299
It's not the pain that gets people to talk.
It's the talking that causes people pain.

32:07.843 --> 32:09.635
So tell me a story.

32:09.803 --> 32:11.929
You told me a story once,
in the warehouse.

32:12.097 --> 32:14.348
Story about your son.

32:15.517 --> 32:18.644
That's when you let me go. Ha.

32:19.187 --> 32:20.688
Looking back on it, it's funny.

32:21.273 --> 32:23.357
You don't strike me
as the sentimental type.

32:23.567 --> 32:25.276
Your story, not mine.

32:26.570 --> 32:28.696
Yeah, but you believed it.

32:31.366 --> 32:33.284
You believed it...

32:34.077 --> 32:36.370
...because you have a child.

32:37.289 --> 32:38.539
I've seen your scar.

32:43.712 --> 32:48.382
My story is your story. That's why you
told it back to me when I asked you.

32:48.592 --> 32:51.385
This is what is important.

32:52.554 --> 32:54.889
This is who you're protecting.

32:57.184 --> 32:59.185
You have a son.

33:00.896 --> 33:02.021
He's your accomplice.

33:08.153 --> 33:09.528
See?

33:10.697 --> 33:12.615
That wasn't so hard.

33:46.274 --> 33:49.735
So your son is your accomplice.

33:50.070 --> 33:53.489
You're not Bonnie. You're Ma Barker.

33:53.782 --> 33:56.701
-He's just a boy.
-A boy you'd die to protect.

33:56.910 --> 33:59.453
Any mother would.

33:59.996 --> 34:01.372
You'd be surprised.

34:02.958 --> 34:05.167
The enemy's like a weed.

34:05.335 --> 34:09.505
You leave any part of it underground, it'll
pop back up when you least expect it.

34:10.382 --> 34:12.133
You gotta kill the root.

34:12.300 --> 34:13.509
[CHUCKLES]

34:13.677 --> 34:15.469
Or in this case...

34:16.179 --> 34:17.930
...the seed.

34:18.682 --> 34:21.809
You won't get anywhere near him.
He's not alone.

34:21.977 --> 34:25.187
I won't have to. You're his mother.

34:29.276 --> 34:30.609
He'll come to you.

34:30.777 --> 34:34.238
He won't come anywhere near here.
He knows better.

34:34.448 --> 34:35.906
He will.

34:39.161 --> 34:40.369
He will when you ask him.

34:48.962 --> 34:50.379
[GASPS]

34:57.596 --> 34:59.430
We don't need to talk anymore.

35:03.727 --> 35:05.853
I won't call him.

35:06.813 --> 35:07.938
I'll die first.

35:08.815 --> 35:11.400
Oh, you'd like that. To die.

35:12.569 --> 35:14.195
But it's never that easy, is it?

35:16.531 --> 35:20.284
Hey. Hey, wake up. You okay?
You called me.

35:20.994 --> 35:22.745
Yes. The nurse. She gave me a shot.

35:26.124 --> 35:27.541
Some kind of sedative.

35:27.751 --> 35:28.876
Let's get out of here.

35:30.587 --> 35:32.463
No. She's going to keep hurting people.

35:34.216 --> 35:36.258
We have to do something.

35:39.721 --> 35:41.722
[KEYPAD CHIRPING]

35:42.057 --> 35:43.349
[LOCK CLICKS]

35:52.192 --> 35:54.652
Think you can hack the combination?

35:54.820 --> 35:56.779
In my sleep.

36:02.452 --> 36:03.661
[KEYPAD CHIRPING]

36:03.829 --> 36:05.496
[LOCK CLICKS]

36:17.425 --> 36:19.134
It's some kind of scanning program.

36:22.013 --> 36:23.722
It's neural activity. Brain scans.

36:27.143 --> 36:28.185
[TYPING]

36:31.481 --> 36:34.149
-There's files. Thousands of them.
-Am I in there?

36:35.735 --> 36:38.070
I don't know. It's by patient number.

36:50.584 --> 36:53.586
All right. There's a ton of data on you.
It's a whole profile.

36:53.795 --> 36:54.920
Delete it. All of it.

36:56.756 --> 36:59.633
It's a Skynet experiment, John.
They're stealing everything.

37:00.927 --> 37:03.345
-No, Mom--
-Sleep is the perfect cover.

37:03.513 --> 37:05.556
Your brain's active
but you don't remember.

37:05.724 --> 37:09.560
-They run a sleep clinic.
-They're not people. Get rid of it.

37:16.192 --> 37:19.069
Nurse Hobson?
There's a problem in room 22. No data.

37:19.237 --> 37:21.614
Ms. Baum's electrodes
must have slipped off again.

37:21.781 --> 37:24.241
Thank you for explaining.

37:27.329 --> 37:28.621
Is that everything?

37:28.830 --> 37:31.123
-Almost.
-I don't want a trace of me left--

37:31.333 --> 37:33.500
-I know.
-All of it. All of it. Get rid of it.

37:33.710 --> 37:35.461
I don't want any of me in there.

37:36.338 --> 37:39.882
All right, it's gone. It's all gone, okay?
You're all gone.

37:41.343 --> 37:44.011
Whatever she gave me,
it's starting to hit.

37:44.804 --> 37:46.805
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

37:48.350 --> 37:49.642
[KEYPAD CHIRPING]

37:51.686 --> 37:52.686
[LOCK CLICKS]

38:01.279 --> 38:03.739
This is a restricted area.
How did you get in here?

38:05.075 --> 38:07.201
I don't know.
I must've been sleepwalking.

38:08.244 --> 38:09.495
Through a locked door?

38:10.789 --> 38:11.830
Sorry.

38:17.003 --> 38:18.629
I'll go back to my room.

38:20.298 --> 38:23.425
Did you know
that when a human falls in love...

38:23.593 --> 38:27.638
...the same areas of the brain
light up as when a human is intoxicated?

38:29.099 --> 38:31.475
What does that have to do
with my nightmares?

38:31.643 --> 38:33.310
We don't know yet.

38:33.478 --> 38:36.438
We don't fully understand
why humans need to dream.

38:38.692 --> 38:40.025
Humans like you?

38:43.279 --> 38:44.530
You drugged me.

38:44.739 --> 38:48.325
What you're experiencing
is sleep paralysis.

38:48.493 --> 38:50.285
You want to move but you can't.

38:56.292 --> 38:57.751
[GASPS]

38:58.378 --> 39:02.631
Believe it or not, your body
is actually protecting you right now.

39:04.175 --> 39:07.594
You were talking to someone
when I entered the room. Your boy.

39:07.762 --> 39:09.096
The one who came to visit.

39:09.889 --> 39:10.931
Call to him.

39:11.725 --> 39:13.684
[GASPS]

39:13.935 --> 39:15.269
I'd die first.

39:17.230 --> 39:20.983
HOBSON:
I'm sure you'd like that. To die.

39:25.572 --> 39:26.780
But it's never that easy.

39:37.250 --> 39:39.084
What is this thing?

39:40.420 --> 39:41.920
Mom.

39:44.049 --> 39:45.090
What are you?

39:52.891 --> 39:54.516
SARAH:
John.

39:56.603 --> 39:57.644
John.

39:58.521 --> 40:00.439
[GUN CLICKING]

40:14.537 --> 40:15.621
[SARAH WHIMPERS]

40:15.789 --> 40:17.664
[MUFFLED SOBBING]

40:22.670 --> 40:24.213
WINSTON:
It's her son.

40:24.422 --> 40:26.757
He's the one who helped her
blow up the facility.

40:26.925 --> 40:28.967
He's the one we want.

40:33.598 --> 40:35.641
We'll give him a few more hours
to show up.

40:36.392 --> 40:38.769
I don't know. Maybe three.

40:46.778 --> 40:51.281
She gave me a few problems.
Nothing I couldn't handle.

40:54.786 --> 40:58.122
Yeah. I guess we don't
need her anymore.

41:03.086 --> 41:07.548
No. He can trace her cell phone without
her alive. Makes no difference to me.

41:09.801 --> 41:14.054
It's not a problem.
I'll take care of it right now.

41:15.265 --> 41:16.306
[EXHALES]

41:16.474 --> 41:19.143
Hell, it's what she wants.

41:28.236 --> 41:29.862
-Aah!
-Uhn!

41:30.155 --> 41:31.905
[GRUNTING]

42:02.729 --> 42:03.770
[GROANING]

42:15.283 --> 42:16.325
You're real.

42:19.412 --> 42:21.914
You're real. You're real.

42:24.834 --> 42:26.752
[GUNSHOT]

42:33.259 --> 42:37.971
SARAH: A spirit sits on a man's chest.
She is strong, beautiful.

42:38.139 --> 42:41.016
She is here to steal his children.

42:41.184 --> 42:43.685
She is here to steal his future.

42:43.853 --> 42:45.020
He is paralyzed.

42:45.188 --> 42:48.315
The terror in him will burst his heart
if he cannot control it.

42:50.902 --> 42:52.819
She is a Night-Mare, a demon-woman...

42:52.987 --> 42:56.615
...the oldest and most enduring story
told by man.

42:57.784 --> 43:00.494
The witching hour is controlled
by witches.

43:08.836 --> 43:11.296
She is a bad dream.

43:17.095 --> 43:19.513
She is a bad bitch.
